metadata.name: Mujer Hongo
metadata.description:
Title: Mujer Hongo
Date: 2021
Photography-based digital manipulation.
The work arises from the idea of ​​representing the end of the life cycle. When our bodies unite with the earth and soil. When the little that remains of a human being serves as food for the flora. 
"Mujer Hongo" is an allusion to the fusion between two living beings with different anatomy. It is a representation of the stability of living systems as a community of fungi and frogs, as well as different roots and rocks.
I seek to represent in the most dreamlike way possible the final stage of death and how life can arise from it.
